<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>My Blog</title><link>https://OneTime24.github.io/</link><description>Recent content on My Blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://OneTime24.github.io/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Beginner Guide: Basic Git and GitHub Commands</title><link>https://OneTime24.github.io/posts/git-baics/</link><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://OneTime24.github.io/posts/git-baics/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="beginner-guide-basic-git-and-github-commands"&gt;Beginner Guide: Basic Git and GitHub Commands&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Git is a distributed version control system used to track changes in code, while GitHub is a platform that allows developers to host and collaborate on Git repositories.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This guide introduces the most important Git and GitHub commands that every beginner should know.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id="1-configure-git"&gt;1. Configure Git&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before using Git, you should configure your username and email.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git config --global user.name &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;OneTime24&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git config --global user.email &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;onetimehexa@gmail.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Basic Git and GitHub Commands</title><link>https://OneTime24.github.io/posts/basic_git_commands/</link><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://OneTime24.github.io/posts/basic_git_commands/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="basic-git-and-github-commands"&gt;Basic Git and GitHub Commands&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is a list of essential commands for working with Git and GitHub:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="1-git-configuration"&gt;1. Git Configuration&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git config --global user.name &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Your Name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git config --global user.email &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;you@example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Introduction</title><link>https://OneTime24.github.io/posts/introduction/</link><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 13:12:13 +0500</pubDate><guid>https://OneTime24.github.io/posts/introduction/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Hello everyone!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is my first Hugo blog post.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>